---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Patient Acquisition" section="patient-acquisition">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Strategy · Patient Acquisition Enablement</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Arm the channel, <em>don't outreach alone.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Leadership's #1 focus. Direct patient outreach is already owned elsewhere — so marketing's play is to build the engine and the ammunition that lets all 5,000 practices convert their own patients into members. Higher-leverage than 1:1, and cleaner on compliance.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>You don't run the direct outreach (someone else does) — you build the system behind it: education content, practice-enablement kits, webinars, retargeting, and email cadences. A practice informing <em>its own</em> patients scales to thousands of offices AND sits on the right side of anti-kickback rules (inform, never incentivize). This is the plan to hand leadership: marketing builds the engine, practices + the existing outreach function run it.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="patient-acquisition"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Builds shipped: <span data-progress-here="patient-acquisition">0 / 0</span></p>

  <h2>The model — <em>why enablement beats outreach.</em></h2>
  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem"><strong>The boundary is a feature, not a limit.</strong> You can't actively reach patients (owned elsewhere) — good, because 1:1 outreach by one function doesn't scale to 5,000 practices. Instead, marketing builds turnkey assets the practices and the existing outreach function deploy. Jim's own insight powers this: front-desk staff can't sell membership (turnover, no sales focus), so <strong>arm them</strong> instead of relying on them.</p>
    <p style="margin:0"><strong>Compliance bonus:</strong> when the <em>practice</em> informs its <em>own</em> patients (practice-branded), the regulatory posture is far stronger than Clerri marketing to strangers' patients. Build everything to be practice-deployable.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="callout wine">
    <div class="lbl">⚠️ The guardrail on everything below</div>
    <p style="margin:0">Anti-kickback / insurance-like rules: <strong>INFORM patients about membership options, never INCENTIVIZE</strong> (no "sign up and get $X"). Get the guardrails signed off with legal before any asset ships. Educational framing only.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>The five pillars</h2>

  <h3>1 · Patient-education content <span class="pill pill-zest">the library</span></h3>
  <div class="card">
    <p>The compliant, reusable asset library every other pillar draws from — purely educational, no inducement.</p>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.6;padding-left:1.2rem;margin:0 0 0.6rem">
      <li>"What is a membership plan / what it covers / what you save / how it works"</li>
      <li>Segment cuts: uninsured, lapsed-insurance, families, seniors</li>
      <li>Formats: explainer pages, FAQ, short videos, one-pagers, an informational savings illustration</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First build:</strong> a 6-8 piece core education set, practice-brandable, that powers the emails, directory, in-office assets, and retargeting landing pages.</p>
    <div data-section="patient-acquisition"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="pa-01-content" data-section="patient-acquisition" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Ship the core patient-education library (practice-brandable)</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>2 · Practice enablement / empowerment <span class="pill pill-zest">arm the channel</span></h3>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Turnkey kits so a busy, high-turnover front desk can present membership without "selling."</p>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.6;padding-left:1.2rem;margin:0 0 0.6rem">
      <li>Co-branded patient-education materials practices send to their own base</li>
      <li>In-office assets: posters, treatment-room cards, QR codes to the education content</li>
      <li>Front-desk talk tracks (informational), a "membership-in-a-box" onboarding kit for new practices</li>
      <li>Drafted email templates practices send to their patients (built by marketing, sent by the practice)</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First build:</strong> the "membership-in-a-box" enablement kit + 3 practice-send email templates.</p>
    <div data-section="patient-acquisition"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="pa-02-enablement" data-section="patient-acquisition" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Build the practice enablement kit + practice-send templates</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>3 · Webinars + education for practices <span class="pill pill-zest">scalable lift</span></h3>
  <div class="card">
    <p>The recurring engine that lifts enrollment velocity across the whole base without 1:1 work.</p>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.6;padding-left:1.2rem;margin:0 0 0.6rem">
      <li>Series: "How to grow your membership plan," "Talking to patients about membership," "The uninsured-patient opportunity"</li>
      <li>Feature high-performers as proof + peer learning (SkyRidge 8X, 7-to-7 $4.5M, Midtown 46% — verify sourcing)</li>
      <li>On-demand library + office hours / customer summit; aspiration drives base-wide adoption</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First build:</strong> a 3-part webinar series + an on-demand recording hub, anchored on a customer success story.</p>
    <div data-section="patient-acquisition"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="pa-03-webinars" data-section="patient-acquisition" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Launch the practice webinar series + on-demand hub</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>4 · Retargeting + demand capture <span class="pill pill-zest">digital engine</span></h3>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Re-engage consumers who showed membership interest but didn't enroll — via the directory, practice pages, and education content.</p>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.6;padding-left:1.2rem;margin:0 0 0.6rem">
      <li>Audiences: directory (Clerri Find) visitors, education-content readers, enrollment-page abandoners</li>
      <li>Channels: Meta, Google display, YouTube — informational creative ("how membership works"), not incentive-based</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="callout" style="margin:0.4rem 0">
      <div class="lbl">⚠️ Healthcare privacy caveat</div>
      <p style="margin:0;font-size:0.875rem">Meta + Google restrict health-related ad targeting, and pixel-based retargeting on health-adjacent sites has triggered HIPAA lawsuits for health systems. Target on <strong>membership-interest behavior</strong> (visited the directory / read membership content), never on health status or PHI. Legal review before pixels go live.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First build:</strong> pixel + audience setup on the directory and education pages, with a legal-reviewed informational retargeting flight.</p>
    <div data-section="patient-acquisition"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="pa-04-retargeting" data-section="patient-acquisition" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Stand up compliant retargeting (legal-reviewed, behavior-based)</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h3>5 · Email cadences <span class="pill pill-zest">automated nurture</span></h3>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Two tracks, both automated:</p>
    <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.6;padding-left:1.2rem;margin:0 0 0.6rem">
      <li><strong>Member/patient track</strong> (informational, practice-branded / via the existing outreach function): welcome + education series, "what your membership covers," <strong>renewal lifecycle</strong> (Jim noted members get only one renewal email/year — a clear retention gap), lapsed re-engagement</li>
      <li><strong>Practice-enablement track:</strong> "here's this month's patient-education asset to send," best practices, webinar invites</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First build:</strong> the patient welcome/education series + a real renewal lifecycle (fixes the once-a-year gap). Built in-house (off 7knots' generic templates).</p>
    <div data-section="patient-acquisition"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="pa-05-email" data-section="patient-acquisition" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Build patient education series + renewal lifecycle (in-house)</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h2>Coordination — <em>so this complements, not collides.</em></h2>
  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card"><h4>The outreach owner</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Whoever runs customer campaigns today (Jacob's product person): you build assets/cadences, they deploy. Align on who sends what so patients/members aren't double-messaged.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Nik (data)</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Clean, separate member list — never message members as prospects. Members stay distinct from the sending lists (the botched-campaign lesson).</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>John (CS)</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">CS owns the practice relationship + the "actively selling vs. onboarded" data. Co-own the webinar/enablement program with CS.</p></div>
  </div>

  <h2>Measurement</h2>
  <div class="callout mint">
    <p style="margin:0">North-star: <strong>enrollment velocity per practice</strong> + member growth rate across the base. Supporting: content engagement, webinar attendance → enrollment lift, renewal rate (vs. the once-a-year baseline), % of practices "actively selling" (John's metric). Tie to HubSpot once member lists + the SF deal-sync are clean.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>90-day build sequence</h2>
  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-mint">Weeks 1-4</span><h4 style="margin:0.4rem 0">Gate + foundations</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Legal guardrails signed off; clean member list with Nik; align with the outreach owner + John. Draft the core education library.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-zest">Weeks 5-8</span><h4 style="margin:0.4rem 0">Ship the kit + cadence</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Practice enablement kit + templates; patient welcome/education email series; renewal lifecycle. First webinar booked around a customer story.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-wine">Weeks 9-12</span><h4 style="margin:0.4rem 0">Turn on the engine</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Compliant retargeting live; webinar series running + on-demand hub; measure enrollment velocity + report per the weekly call.</p></div>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Patient acquisition notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="patient-acquisition-notes" placeholder="Legal sign-offs, coordination with the outreach owner/Nik/John, what's converting, enrollment-velocity data..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/segment-plan"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">Segment Marketing Plan</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/market"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">Market Context</span></a>
  </div>

</div>

<style>
  .card .grab { background:rgba(207,252,120,0.18); border-left:3px solid var(--clerri-green); padding:0.5rem 0.75rem; border-radius:0 0.4rem 0.4rem 0; font-size:0.9rem; }
  h3 .pill { vertical-align:middle; margin-left:0.4rem; font-size:0.6rem; }
</style>

</ClerriLayout>
